default2. How effective is horizon scanning in Government? Do Ministers and senior officials consider horizon scanning outputs appropriately?
default2.1 As noted above, it is
default not felt that horizon scanning outputs are used as effectively as they could be, or that there is obvious follow up on the recommendations made in horizon scanning activities. It is also felt that individual departments’ efforts at horizon scanning have b
defaulteen uncoordinated and sometimes mutually contradictory.
default2.2 One challenge for government departments is that they receive a wealth of external reports, which unfortunately are only useful if they reach the appropriate senior civil servant at exactly the ri
defaultght time due to the precise government timetables they work to. Reports can only be of real benefit if they are on an agenda set by Ministers or by external events.
default&#xa0;
defaultFor this reason, better on
default-
defaultgoing communications between government and the external bodies 
defaultthat can produce valuable horizon scanning is needed to ensure that information is received when it is of use.
default2.3 A key tool in horizon 
defaultscanning is scenario planning. 
defaultEffective horizon scanning by government would involve setting out possible scenarios wh
defaultich are not predictions or even extrapolations, but are credible possible futures against which government could 
defaultsay that, if this scenario were to arise, the legislative and policy actions needed would be X, Y and Z.
default&#xa0;
defaultUnfortunately scenario planning has a 
defaultchequered history in 
defaultg
defaultovernment 
defaultd
defaultepartments 
defaultand is considered as labour intensive for policy-makers.
default2.4 In terms of technological foresight, the relevant technical expertise to deliver
default tends to be found within the public delivery agencies rather than cent
defaultral 
defaultg
defaultovernment (there are more 
defaultprofessional
default engineers in Ofgem than there are in DECC, for example). 
default&#xa0;
defaultMany issues that could benefit from foresight are dealt with by the devolved administrations, with, for example,
default&#xa0;
defaultTfL in contact with the cutting edge 
defaultof technology rather than DfT. 
